Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.06,辉注,,0,0,0,,对应子镜面编号A B C
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.91,0:03:37.17,辉注,,0,0,0,,18块子镜被分成10组 每组两块子镜\N其中C2和C5镜面被同时分配给两组\N所以是"10组 20块子镜"\N子镜的标号可以看本视频2:13画面右侧
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.81,0:03:44.19,辉注,,0,0,0,,译注: 平移误差越大 条纹越密集\N平移误差的符号不同 条纹的倾斜方向相反
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:49.84,辉注,,0,0,0,,译注: 粗->精->粗->精->粗->精
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:11.61,辉注,,0,0,0,,译注: 2022年2月25日 第三步图像堆叠已完成
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.43,0:00:05.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯·韦布空间望远镜终于上天了 但要做的工作还有很多
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.43,0:00:05.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,The James Webb telescope is finally in space, but the work has not stopped there.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.45,0:00:10.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,光学组件需要进行调整才能让我们看到宇宙遥远的过去
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.45,0:00:10.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,The optical instruments need to work for it to send us clear images of our distant past.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.37,0:00:15.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有18块六边形镜面都要进行10纳米精度的调整
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.37,0:00:15.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,All the eighteen hexagonal mirror segments must align within ten nanometers of one another
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.48,0:00:18.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,才能组成一整块主镜
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.48,0:00:18.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,to form a single big primary mirror.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.33,0:00:20.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,说说容易 做起来难
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.33,0:00:20.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, that sounds easier said than done
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.76,0:00:23.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为镜面调整所需的10纳米精度
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.76,0:00:23.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,because achieving this aim requires making fine adjustments
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.83,0:00:27.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,只有人类头发丝直径的万分之一
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.83,0:00:27.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,as small as 1/10,000th the width of a human hair.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:27.21,0:00:31.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些调整阶段称为调相
Dialogue: 2,0:00:27.21,0:00:31.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,The phase during which these adjustments take place is known as phasing.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.67,0:00:35.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,镜面调整前后要耗时至少三个月
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.67,0:00:35.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember that these adjustments can take at least three months to execute.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.55,0:00:40.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这一切都完成后 望远镜的完全体就出来了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.55,0:00:40.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, once the process is complete, the telescope will finally fulfill its function.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.53,0:00:45.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,镜面调整流程一共分为七个阶段: 子镜面图像识别
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.53,0:00:45.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,The mirror alignment process includes seven phases: segment image identification,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.69,0:00:50.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,子镜面调整 图像堆叠 粗调相 精调相
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.69,0:00:50.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,segment alignment, image stacking, coarse phasing, fine phasing,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.53,0:00:53.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,基于仪器视场的望远镜调整 和基于仪器视场的迭代调整
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.53,0:00:53.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,telescope alignment over instrument fields of view,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:53.41,0:00:55.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,基于仪器视场的望远镜调整 和基于仪器视场的迭代调整
Dialogue: 2,0:00:53.41,0:00:55.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,and iterate alignment for final correction.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.96,0:00:58.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们一起看看每个步骤的具体细节 来了解整个镜面调整的流程吧
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.96,0:00:58.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let's look at each of these phases in detail
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.23,0:01:01.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们一起看看每个步骤的具体细节 来了解整个镜面调整的流程吧
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.23,0:01:01.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,to understand how the entire process will take place.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.54,0:01:05.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,第一阶段需要调整望远镜与航天器整体的关系
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.54,0:01:05.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first phase requires the alignment of the telescope in relation to the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.04,0:01:09.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,需要用到星敏感器引导航天器精确指向
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.04,0:01:09.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,It will use star trackers to make precise pointing moves,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.39,0:01:12.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,而星敏感器对于航天器的作用就像GPS一样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:09.39,0:01:12.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,as these star trackers work as a GPS for the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.77,0:01:15.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,最开始 星敏感器引导航天器的方向和各个子镜的指向并不一致
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.77,0:01:15.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,Initially, the spacecraft position from the star tracker
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.61,0:01:18.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,最开始 星敏感器引导航天器的方向和各个子镜的指向并不一致
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.61,0:01:18.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,will not match the mirror segment positions.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.24,0:01:24.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后 望远镜会指向一个孤立的亮星(HD 84406)
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.24,0:01:24.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,Later on, the telescope is pointed towards an isolated and bright star (HD 84406)
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.79,0:01:28.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,捕捉到的图像被汇集到一起 拼一张星空的照片
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.79,0:01:28.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,to capture images that are brought together to form a picture of the sky.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.78,0:01:33.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,当然 别忘了 拍摄星空的子镜不只有一块 而是18块
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.78,0:01:33.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, you must remember that there is not just one mirror looking at the sky
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.21,0:01:35.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,当然 别忘了 拍摄星空的子镜不只有一块 而是18块
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.21,0:01:35.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,as there are eighteen mirrors,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.32,0:01:39.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,每一块子镜最初都是各自为战 朝向星空的某一个点
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.32,0:01:39.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,each of which is tilted at the beginning towards a unique part of the sky.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.30,0:01:43.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此 望远镜最后会得到18份目标恒星的照片
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.30,0:01:43.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because of this, the telescope will capture eighteen copies of the star,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.52,0:01:46.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,每个都是失焦的 且有不同程度的失真
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.52,0:01:46.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,each one is out  of focus and has a unique distortion.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.10,0:01:51.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,最初拍摄的这些目标恒星照片称为子镜图像
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.10,0:01:51.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,These initial star copies from the telescope are known as segment images.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.64,0:01:53.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,根据每块子镜初始位置不同
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.64,0:01:53.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Depending on the mirror's starting positions,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.77,0:01:58.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,可能需要多次迭代才能确定每个图片对应哪块子镜
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.77,0:01:58.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,it might take many iterations to locate all the eighteen segments from a single image.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.95,0:02:00.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,而NASA的工作就是要通过移动这些子镜
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.95,0:02:00.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,The job of the space agency
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.92,0:02:04.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,而NASA的工作就是要通过移动这些子镜
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.92,0:02:04.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,is to move the eighteen mirror segments to understand
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.08,0:02:06.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,来确定哪个图像对应哪个子镜
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.08,0:02:06.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,which segment creates which segment image.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.81,0:02:09.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,当这些图像都找准谁是谁后
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.81,0:02:09.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once the matching of the segment is done to the image,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.29,0:02:12.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,各子镜会把它们移动到对应其自身位置的点
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.29,0:02:12.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,the mirrors are tilted to bring all of the images near a common point.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:13.11,0:02:18.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样可以进一步辅助图像的分析 这样排列后称为图像阵列
Dialogue: 2,0:02:13.11,0:02:18.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,It helps analyze the image further, and such an arrangement is known as an image array.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.88,0:02:22.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,镜面调整的第二步是子镜面调整
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.88,0:02:22.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,The second phase of mirror alignment is segment alignment,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.31,0:02:26.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个过程可以修正子镜面的大部分定位误差
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.31,0:02:26.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is a process that corrects most of the positioning errors of the mirror segments.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.95,0:02:30.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,该过程首先要轻微移动副镜 让子镜图像离焦
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.95,0:02:30.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,The process begins by defocusing the segment images
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.32,0:02:32.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,该过程首先要轻微移动副镜 让子镜图像散焦
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.32,0:02:32.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,by moving the secondary mirror slightly.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.77,0:02:38.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,当然 离焦这一步骤并不容易 执行背后需要数学上的分析
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.77,0:02:38.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, defocusing is not easy and requires mathematical analysis to execute.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.35,0:02:43.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,子镜面调整完成 相当于有了18个完成校准的望远镜
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.35,0:02:43.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Once it is done, the segment adjustment leads to eighteen well-corrected telescopes.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:43.51,0:02:48.03,辉中,,0,0,0,,但请记住 此步骤完成后 它们仍然是各自为战
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.51,0:02:48.03,辉英,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that the segments are still not working as a single mirror during this phase.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.14,0:02:51.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,接下来是第三步 图像堆叠
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.14,0:02:51.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,We move onto the third phase, which is known as image stacking.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.18,0:02:56.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,这步中 我们要把所有子镜图像堆叠到一起 以便汇聚光线
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.18,0:02:56.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,During this phase, each segmented image must be stacked on top of one another
Dialogue: 1,0:02:56.81,0:02:59.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,这步中 我们要把所有子镜图像堆叠到一起 以便汇聚光线
Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.81,0:02:59.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,to put all the light in one place.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.30,0:03:01.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后 每个子镜图像会单独调整
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.30,0:03:01.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then, the individual segment images are moved
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.99,0:03:05.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,让图像落在视场中心 形成统一的图像
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.99,0:03:05.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that they fall at the field's center to produce a unified image.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.53,0:03:10.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,第三步可以为第四步的"粗调相"做准备
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.53,0:03:10.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,The third phase prepares the telescope for the fourth phase, which is Coarse Phasing.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,并且图像堆叠会把子镜分为三组依次进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,The image stacking is one in a sequence in groups of three.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.16,0:03:17.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,粗调相要把所有子镜面对齐
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.16,0:03:17.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,During the fourth phase, the segments must be in line with one another
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.96,0:03:22.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,误差要小于光的波长
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.96,0:03:22.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the precision and accuracy of something smaller than the wavelength of light.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.59,0:03:24.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,粗调相本质就是测量并修正子镜面之间的垂直位移误差
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.59,0:03:24.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,Coarse Phasing is used to measure and correct
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.89,0:03:27.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,粗调相本质就是测量并修正子镜面之间的垂直位移误差
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.89,0:03:27.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,the vertical displacement of the mirror's segments.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.49,0:03:31.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一步涉及到"色散条纹传感"技术
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.49,0:03:31.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,The technology used during this phase is called Dispersed Fringe Sensing,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.91,0:03:34.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,要用到近红外相机提取10组 20块子镜的光谱信号
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.91,0:03:34.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the NIRCam is used to capture light spectra
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.52,0:03:37.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,要用到近红外相机提取10组 20块子镜的光谱信号
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.52,0:03:37.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,from twenty separate pairings of the mirror segments.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.27,0:03:39.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,采集的光谱信号图样如视频所示
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.27,0:03:39.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,The spectrum will look like a barber pole pattern
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.81,0:03:44.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,条纹的斜率与疏密可以反映出两块子镜之间的平移误差
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.81,0:03:44.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,with an angle or slope determined by the two segments and their piston difference.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.35,0:03:49.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,第四步的粗调相和第五步的精调相交替进行三次
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.35,0:03:49.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fifth phase, also known as Fine Phasing, is done three times after the fourth phase.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,并且在望远镜的整个寿命周期内都要定期进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,Besides that, it will also be done routinely
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.47,0:03:54.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,并且在望远镜的整个寿命周期内都要定期进行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.47,0:03:54.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,from time to time during the lifespan of Webb.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.03,0:03:59.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一步会使用离焦法修正之前调整后剩余的误差
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.03,0:03:59.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,The phase corrects the leftover alignment errors using the defocusing method.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.47,0:04:03.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,不过这次不会再使用到副镜
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.47,0:04:03.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, the secondary mirror is not used during this phase.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.16,0:04:06.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,而是使用科学仪器内部的特殊光学元件
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.16,0:04:06.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,Instead, special optical elements inside the instrument are used
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.82,0:04:10.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,为每个图像引入不同的离焦量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.82,0:04:10.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,that introduce various defocusing amounts for each image.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.48,0:04:15.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,下一步 基于仪器视场的望远镜调整
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.48,0:04:15.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,After this phase, it is time for the telescope alignment over instrument fields of view.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.46,0:04:20.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一步中 调整会涉及到剩余的科学仪器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.46,0:04:20.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,During this phase, the alignment will be extended to the remaining instruments.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.07,0:04:24.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,多个科学仪器的多个视场点都会进行测量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.07,0:04:24.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,The measurements are made at multiple field points across the various science instruments.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.02,0:04:29.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,若某视场点的信号强度有明显差别 说明此处有较大的误差
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.02,0:04:29.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,The variation in intensity indicates that there are larger errors at that field point.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.07,0:04:33.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,于是 人们会用一个算法计算最终需要的修正量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.07,0:04:33.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, an algorithm will calculate the final corrections required
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.37,0:04:37.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而让望远镜上所有科学仪器都能达到完美校准的状态
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.37,0:04:37.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,to achieve the perfect telescope alignment across all the science instruments.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.03,0:04:43.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,最后一步 为最终修正进行的迭代调整
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.03,0:04:43.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,Finally, we have the last phase, which is the iterate alignment for final correction.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.27,0:04:46.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一步骤可以确保所有小的定位误差在主镜中得到纠正或消除
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.27,0:04:46.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,The final augment ensures that all small positioning errors
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.75,0:04:49.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,这一步骤可以确保所有小的定位误差在主镜中得到纠正或消除
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.75,0:04:49.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,are corrected or removed in the primary mirror.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.91,0:04:53.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们会使用第五步的精调相来进行测量与修正
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.91,0:04:53.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fine phasing process is used to measure and make any corrections.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.90,0:04:57.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后会对每一个科学仪器的成像质量进行一次快速检查
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.90,0:04:57.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,After that, an image quality check is done across all the instruments,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.78,0:05:02.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果质检通过 那么这一步就完成了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.78,0:05:02.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,and once verification of the quality is done, the process is complete.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.31,0:05:03.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,这七个步骤将确保望远镜主镜能被正确校准
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.31,0:05:03.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,These are the seven phases
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.83,0:05:07.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,这七个步骤将确保望远镜主镜能被正确校准
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.83,0:05:07.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,that will ensure the proper alignment of the primary mirror of the telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.85,0:05:11.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,此时 JWST团队已完成前三步
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.85,0:05:11.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,As of now, the Webb team has completed three phases out of the seven.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.80,0:05:14.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,当然 这些步骤全部完成还要些时日
Dialogue: 2,0:05:11.80,0:05:14.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Of course, completing the phases will take time,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.41,0:05:19.86,辉中,,0,0,0,,但完成后 我们就可以正式开始用它执行科学观测了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.41,0:05:19.86,辉英,,0,0,0,,but once it is done, we will finally be in a position to start using the telescope for its purpose.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.01,0:05:21.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,夏日来临之际
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.01,0:05:21.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,By the summer months,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.27,0:05:25.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST将会藉由其巨大的主镜传来第一张清晰的图像
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.27,0:05:25.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,Webb will finally send one of its clear images through this primary mirror.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.57,0:05:30.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,希望JWST后续能一帆风顺 如履平地
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.57,0:05:30.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, everything will go as planned, and the telescope will not go through any hiccups.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.53,0:05:35.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,期待镜面校准完成的那一天
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.53,0:05:35.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,We are excited to see where this goes and when the final mirror alignment takes place.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.62,0:05:37.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,你们也期待吗?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.62,0:05:37.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Are you as excited as us?
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,欢迎在评论区唠嗑
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Let us know in the comments below,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.05,0:05:42.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,期待大家的反馈
Dialogue: 2,0:05:39.05,0:05:42.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we would love to hear your thoughts on this entire process.
